	p This is the Privacy Policy of /name of our company (the Company, we, or us). The Company is registered in _________ with company number _______ and its registered office located at _____________.
	p We are committed to protecting your privacy. Please read this Privacy Policy to understand how we collect and use the information you provide to us when you visit this website, use our products and services, or contact us.
	p Your use of our website, products, and services means unconditional acceptance of this Policy and the personal information processing conditions specified herein. If you disagree with this Policy, you should immediately stop using our website, products, and services.
	p This Privacy Policy is applied to this website, products, and services (Services) of the Company through which we collect personal information and which refer to this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy does not apply to the Company's websites that do not have a link to this Privacy Policy or contain a link to a document other than this Privacy Policy regarding the processing of personal information.
	p In this Privacy Policy, we disclose how we process personal information when using the Company's Internet sites. Being the experts on protection of various types of infrastructures, devices, and data, we understand the importance of an appropriate approach to privacy and data security and adhere to the principle of comprehensive and complete protection of our users' personal information.
	h3 1. General information
	p Personal information means information that identifies, relates to, describes, is capable of being associated with, or could reasonably be linked, directly or indirectly, with a particular consumer or household. In other words, personal information includes all information that can identify a person or household. For example, last name, first name, middle name, patronymic, job title, CV, email address, telephone number, and other information.
	p Personal information also includes technical information if it can identify an individual. For example, IP address, type of operating system, type of device (personal computer, mobile phone, tablet), type of browser, geographic location, the fact of filling in the web form, and Internet provider.
	p If we cannot relate the information to the individual in any way, we will not treat this information as personal information.
	p You understand that we only process personal information that we have received from you, as from an individual using our website and Services.
	p This Privacy Policy defines the Company's policy of processing and protection of personal information and is available at _______. The Company also provides unrestricted access to the Privacy Policy to any person who has personally contacted the Company.
	p The Company may process personal information both with or without the use of automation means. Such processes may include without limitation collection, recording, systematization, accumulation, storage, changing (updating, modification), electronic copying, extraction, use, transmission (distribution, provision, access), depersonalization, removal, and destruction of personal information.
	p The Company processes and stores personal information on servers located on the territory of ____________.
	p The Company does not verify the reliability of the personal information provided by an individual and his or her legal capacity. You guarantee that all data are true, up-to-date, and do not violate relevant legislation on personal information.
	h3 2. What information we collect
	p We may collect:
	ul
		li your email address;
		li record of your correspondence with us, including any information that you provide to us in your messages and emails;
		li information you provide to us to receive technical assistance or during customer service interactions;
		li information about your computer or device, including browser type and settings, IP address and traffic data relating to your Internet connection;
		li information automatically obtained when you access our Services, including access to our websites using cookies;
		li product performance data and information about how you use our products and services; and
		li aggregated data or other information that does not specifically identify you, such as actions taken on our website.
	h3 3. How we collect your information
	ul
		li on our websites and Services;
		li by you signing up for our products or services;
		li in response to marketing or promotional communications; and
		li in connection with an actual or potential business.
	h3 4. Purposes and legal basis of processing. How we use your information
	p We may use your information to:
	ul
		li provide access to our Services;
		li provide, facilitate, and support our products and services;
		li perform the contract we have with you;
		li manage your registered user account;
		li identify you as a user;
		li get feedbacks from you, communicate with you, and respond to your requests;
		li deliver newsletters, product updates, and technical alerts;
		li evaluate, analyze, and improve our products and services, for example by collecting feedback from you;
		li secure our systems and applications;
		li allow you to view the information on our website;
		li provide you with a customized experience when you visit our website; and
		li enforce our legal rights and comply with law.
	p To get in touch with you, the Company may use the telephone number and email address provided by you.
	p We process your data in accordance with the above stated purposes on the basis of the contract serving as the legal ground. If processing is made under consent of the data subject as a different legal basis, such consent shall be taken separately.
	p We collect your email for responding to your queries or sending you our software trial version, we request you to provide your name to be able to personalize our communication with you. For faster response, we may also ask you for your phone number; however, in some forms provision of this information is optional. Your data is important to us for proper provision of our services to you. We will not be able to provide our services to you without this data.
	h3 5. How long we keep your information
	p We keep your information only for as long as it is necessary for the purposes for which it was collected, or as required by law. We keep your information collected on our website for the following terms:
	ul
		li information collected through the form is kept for the term necessary for the performance of our Services to you;
		li statistical data is kept for the term of 90 days; and
		li archived information is kept for the term of five years.
	h3 6. How we protect your information
	p We are committed to ensuring security of your information. We make every effort to hold your information secure in accordance with our internal security procedures and applicable law. Appropriate security measures are in place to protect against loss, misuse, or alteration of your information. Specifically, we use the following measures to protect your personal information:
	ul
		li we do not sell the personal information of California consumers and do not discriminate in response to privacy rights requests;
		li we do not track our customers over time and across third party websites to provide targeted advertising and therefore do not respond to Do Not Track (DNT) signals;
		li we do not take any decisions involving the use of algorithms or profiling that significantly affect you;
		li we develop local regulations of the Company implementing the requirements of personal information legislation;
		li we refuse from personal information processing if the methods of such processing do not meet the purposes of processing predefined by the Company;
		li we grant access to personal information to a limited number of people;
		li we ensure that those persons who have access to personal information, have read and understood the applicable laws on the processing and protection of the personal information;
		li we apply cryptographic protection instruments to information containing personal information;
		li we restrict access to information resources and data processing facilities;
		li we use antivirus tools for personal information security system;
		li we restrict access to the Company's premises;
		li we appoint the person responsible for processing of personal information (you can contact this person using the following email address: ___________);
		li we perform periodic assessment of risks related to the processing of personal information;
		li we conduct internal investigations to detect facts related to unauthorized access to personal information;
		li we train our employees related to personal information processing; and
		li we ensure that both the Company and third parties that are involved into personal information processing shall maintain confidentiality of personal information and shall not use personal information without legal grounds for processing.
	h3 7. How we share your information. International data transfers
	p Positive Technologies is an international company. That is why we may transfer your personal information to recipients outside the country where you are located. Data protection laws in those countries may differ from the country in which you initially provided the information. We will protect all personal information transfers to other countries as described in this Privacy Policy. By submitting your information to us, you agree to the transfer of your information abroad for the fulfilment of your voluntary requests. To meet the purposes for which your information was collected, we may transfer your data to the following countries: Ireland (Google Analytics), U.S. (Google Analytics, Microsoft Office 365, HubSpot), Germany (Amazon Web Services hosting), Malta (Hotjar), and Poland (GetResponse). When it is necessary to meet the purposes for which your information was collected, we may also share your information with other companies operating under Positive Technologies brand on the following territories: UK, Italy, Czech Republic, Russia, Brazil, and South Korea.
	p Whenever we share or transfer your information, we do so in accordance with this Privacy Policy and the law, and take all reasonable steps to ensure that your information is treated securely. We use approved Standard Contractual Clauses for the international transfer of personal information collected in the European Economic Area and Switzerland.
	p We may disclose your information to law enforcement and other government agencies if we are obliged to do so by law.
	p We may also share your information with third parties, including but not limited to service providers who process information on our behalf, including providers of information technology, website hosting and management, data analysis, data backup, security and storage services, as well as to consultants, partners, providers under the agreements, and agents.
	p We may also transfer your personal information to the third parties stated below and for the following purposes:
	h3 Google Analytics
	p Google Analytics uses traffic log cookies to gain information about the use that is made of pages on our website. We use this information to generate reports on how our website is used to help us improve it. We do not retain any data specific to any identifiable user. The services are provided by Google LLC and Google Inc., located at 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, United States, as well as Google Ireland Limited (as applicable), located at Google Building Gordon House, 4 Barrow St, Dublin, D04 E5W5, Ireland (collectively "Google"). All information is processed by Google in compliance with Privacy Shield and Data Processing Amendment to the Google Analytics Agreement, including cross-border processing. To get more information about how Google processes your personal information, please see its Privacy Policy.
	h3 Microsoft Office 365
	p Microsoft Office 365 is a cloud-based subscription service that offers tools to work with documents and e-mail in such apps like Excel and Outlook. The services are provided by Microsoft Corporation, located at One Microsoft Way, Redmond, WA 98052-6399, USA. All information is processed by Microsoft Corporation in compliance with Privacy Shield, including cross-border processing. To get more information about how Microsoft Corporation processes your personal information, please see its Privacy Statement.
	h3 Hotjar
	p Hotjar tool allows us to gather information about how you use our website. With its help we analyze your behavior and we gather statistics. The services are provided by Hotjar Ltd, located at 3, Elia Zammit Street, St Julians, STJ 3155, Malta, Europe. To get more information about how Hojar processes your personal information, please see its Privacy Policy.
	h3 GetResponse
	p GetResponse is an internet-marketing complex platform, which includes tool for various business purposes, such as e-mail marketing, webinars, landings, and CRM. We use this service to send you marketing e-mails and newsletters, if you are subscribed to them. The services are provided by GetResponse LLC, located at Gdansk (80-387), Arkonska 6, A3, Poland. To get more information about how GetResponse processes your personal information, please see GetResponse Privacy Policy.
	h3 Yandex.Metrica
	p Yandex.Metrica is a web analytics service that tracks and reports website traffic. Yandex.Metrica tool allows us to gather information about how you use our website. With its help we analyze your behavior and we gather statistics. The services are provided by YANDEX, LLC, located at Ulitsa Lva Tolstogo 16, Moscow, Russia 119021. To get more information about how YANDEX processes your personal information, please see its Terms of Use and Privacy Policy.
	h3 8. Profiling
	p Profiling means any form of automated processing of personal information that divides natural persons into groups (profiles) depending on their behavior, interests, and more specific characteristics. We do profiling by means of Google Analytics. You can find more details here: About Demographics and Interests. In any case, your data processed for profiling purposes will not be transferred to third parties and publically shared.
	h3 9. Third-party websites
	p Our website may contain links to other websites of interest. However, we do not have any control over other websites and cannot be responsible for the protection of any information that you may provide them.
	p We encourage you to exercise caution and look at privacy statements on the websites you visit after you leave our website.
	h3 10. Termination of personal information
	p We terminate your personal information in the following cases:
	ul
		li there is a threat to Services' security;
		li the purposes of personal information processing were achieved;
		li there is no further need to achieve the purposes of personal information processing;
		li you violated the terms of this Policy;
		li the term of personal information storage has expired;
		li the contract has expired or was terminated; and
		li you requested us to do so, or if you recalled your consent to process personal information.
	h3 11. How you can control your information
	p Please contact our data protection officer (DPO) at dpo@ptsecurity.com for any queries related to your personal information, including:
	ul
		li The right to opt-out of the sale of your personal information. We do not sell your personal information.
		li The right to request a copy of the information we hold about you if you would like a copy of some or all of your personal information.
		li If you believe that any information we hold about you is incorrect or incomplete, please, send us an email to let us know which information should be updated or deleted.
		li The right to erase your personal information if you no longer want us to process it.
		li The right to restrict our processing of your data when such restriction is applicable to you under the relevant data protection legislation.
	p We will respond to your request to access, amend, or delete your information or to any other queries related to your personal information processing within 45 days as of the date of receipt of your request. This term may be extended once by an additional 45 days when reasonably necessary, provided we notify you of the extension within the first 45-day period.
	p You may also lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority when you believe your personal information is processed unlawfully.
	h3 12. Cookies
	p A cookie is a piece of text that is entered into the memory of your browser by a website, allowing the website to store information on your machine and later retrieve it.
	p We use cookies so that we can remember the language in which you use our website, and better serve you when you return to our website.
	h3 13. Changes to this Policy
	p We keep this Privacy Policy under regular review. The Company has the right to make changes to the Policy, if necessary. Mandatory update of Privacy Policy is made in case of significant changes in international or national personal information legislation. The revised Privacy Policy will apply from the date when it is posted on our website. The date when the revised Privacy Policy is coming into effect will be stated in the Privacy Policy. You should check this page occasionally to ensure that you are happy with any changes. We will notify you of any changes to the Privacy Policy to your email address if we process your personal information.
	p This Privacy Policy was created with brevity and clarity in mind. We will be happy to provide you with any additional information or explanation you may need. Please send your questions and comments to <a href="mailto:dpo@ptsecurity.com">dpo@ptsecurity.com</a>.